value.title: Biden's stimulus provides larger single-year tax breaks than Trump's or Reagan's cuts
value.excerpt: The multitude of tax breaks in the $1.9 trillion relief package signed this month by President Joe Biden will provide one of the biggest one-year tax cuts in modern history, a new analysis has found.

value.title: Biden on US meeting looming Afghanistan withdrawal deadline: 'Could happen, but it is tough'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said he is still making a decision on withdrawing all US troops from Afghanistan ahead of a May 1 deadline set by former President Donald Trump, saying it "could happen, but it is tough."

value.title: Harris condemns 'tragic' Atlanta shooting and expresses solidarity with Asian American community
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris addressed the recent lethal shootings at a series of spas in the Atlanta area, marking her most formal remarks about the ongoing issue of violence against the Asian American community.

value.title: Biden says Putin 'will pay a price' for Russian efforts to undermine 2020 US election
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said Vladimir Putin "will pay a price" for his efforts to undermine the 2020 US election following a landmark American intelligence assessment which found that the Russian government meddled in the 2020 election with the aim of "denigrating" Biden's candidacy.

value.title: New US intel report shows Russia, Trump and GOP acolytes have same goals
value.excerpt: A new US intelligence report that finds Russia interfered in the 2020 election to help Donald Trump and hurt Joe Biden also underscores a fundamental truth: The gravest threat to US democracy comes from within.

value.title: Biden to celebrate St. Patrick's Day virtually with Ireland's prime minister
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden will host Taioseach Micheál Martin of Ireland for a virtual bilateral meeting on Wednesday to celebrate St. Patrick's Day, the White House says, in yet another traditional head of state visit changed by the pandemic.

value.title: Trump urges Americans to get Covid-19 vaccine: 'I would recommend it'
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Tuesday urged Americans to get vaccinated to help curb the Covid-19 pandemic, calling it "safe" and "something that works."

value.title: Harris uses UN speech to champion women's role in democracy
value.excerpt: Kamala Harris declared "the status of women is the status of democracy" on Tuesday, in her first speech before the United Nations as the first female vice president of the United States.

value.title: GOP targets "Biden border crisis" in new ad campaign aimed at battleground districts
value.excerpt: Republicans are ramping up their attacks on Democrats over the ongoing crisis at the Southern border, including a new ad campaign accusing President Joe Biden of opening the border instead of focusing on opening schools and businesses.

value.title: Agency review finds some Trump administration CDC guidance was not grounded in science or free from undue influence
value.excerpt: A review of the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's Covid-19 guidance has found that some of the agency's guidance during the Trump administration was not grounded in science or free from undue influence, according to a statement from a CDC spokesperson.

value.title: Biden says Cuomo investigation is 'underway and we should see what it brings us'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said Sunday he wants to see what comes of an investigation into allegations of sexual harassment against New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo when asked if the Democratic governor should resign.

value.title: Biden commits to 'free, open, secure' Indo-Pacific in rare op-ed with 'Quad' members
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden declared the United States is "committed to a free, open, secure and prosperous Indo-Pacific region" in a rare op-ed penned with the leaders of India, Australia and Japan.

value.title: Analysis: How early pandemic praise for Cuomo, Newsom and Trump disappeared
value.excerpt: Nearly a year ago, New York Democratic Gov. Andrew Cuomo announced that all nonessential workers in the state would have to stay home. The announcement was one of many that marked the beginning of the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: McConnell quietly courts Senate primary candidates 'who can win' regardless of Trump ties
value.excerpt: Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell is quietly maneuvering to field a slate of GOP Senate candidates in critical battleground states, attempting to avoid a repeat of election cycles a decade ago when candidates emerged from primaries only to implode and deny his party the chance to take back the majority.

value.title: Alex Jones allegedly threatened to throw Trump rally organizer off a stage
value.excerpt: Police in Washington, DC, are investigating an allegation that conspiracy theorist Alex Jones threatened to push a pro-Trump political organizer off of an event stage in December, according to people familiar with the incident.

value.title: Joe Biden just can't quit Delaware -- even as president
value.excerpt: Bidding farewell to his adopted home state in January, Joe Biden -- then the President-elect -- grew emotional as he boarded his flight to Washington for the inauguration.

value.title: New York prosecutor investigating Trump announces he won't seek reelection
value.excerpt: The New York prosecutor leading the most significant criminal probe against Donald Trump and his business announced Friday he is not running for reelection, putting the spotlight on who will be elected to take over the investigation into the former president and his business.

value.title: Trump's acting defense secretary says his January 6 speech incited Capitol rioters
value.excerpt: Former acting Secretary of Defense Christopher Miller believes former President Donald Trump's speech on the morning of January 6 incited the rioters who stormed the US Capitol.

value.title: Trump, estranged from Presidents Club, excluded from predecessors' PSA
value.excerpt: When President Donald Trump received his Covid-19 vaccine at the White House in January, it was not recorded by official photographers or videographers, according to a person familiar with the matter, who said it wasn't clear there was any photographic documentation of the moment.

value.title: Trump expected to meet with Sen. Rick Scott amid GOP divide over former President
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump is expected to meet with Republican Sen. Rick Scott this week, a source familiar with the meeting told CNN, at a time when the party is heatedly debating Trump's role in its future.

value.title: Manchin on his veto power over Biden agenda: 'It's not a good place to be'
value.excerpt: In a 50-50 Senate, with most members voting the party-line, Sen. Joe Manchin stands mostly alone: effectively holding veto power over many of President Joe Biden's nominees and key elements of his agenda.

value.title: Senior Biden administration officials to meet with Chinese counterparts next week in Alaska
value.excerpt: Two top Biden administration officials will meet with their Chinese counterparts next week in what will be the first meeting of officials from both countries since President Joe Biden took office in January.

value.title: Trump requests mail-in ballot ahead of local Florida election despite baseless fraud claims
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump requested a mail-in ballot ahead of a local municipal election in Florida, according to Palm Beach County records, despite his frequent attacks on voting by mail.
